# Neon Database (for everything)
VITE_NEON_DATABASE_URL=postgresql://username:password@your-neon-project-url/dbname?sslmode=require

# JWT Secret for authentication (change in production!)
VITE_JWT_SECRET=your-super-secret-jwt-key-change-this-in-production

# Google OAuth 2.0
VITE_GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID=your-google-client-id
VITE_GOOGLE_CLIENT_SECRET=your-google-client-secret
VITE_GOOGLE_OAUTH_REDIRECT_URI=http://localhost:5173/auth/google/callback

# GitHub OAuth 2.0
VITE_GITHUB_CLIENT_ID=your-github-client-id
VITE_GITHUB_CLIENT_SECRET=your-github-client-secret
VITE_GITHUB_OAUTH_REDIRECT_URI=http://localhost:5173/auth/github/callback

# Email Service (SMTP)
VITE_SMTP_HOST=smtp.gmail.com
VITE_SMTP_PORT=587
VITE_SMTP_USERNAME=your-email@gmail.com
VITE_SMTP_PASSWORD=your-smtp-password
VITE_SMTP_FROM=noreply@quizsystem.com
VITE_SMTP_SECURE=true

# S3 Storage
VITE_S3_BUCKET_NAME=your-bucket-name
VITE_S3_AWS_REGION=us-east-1
VITE_S3_ACCESS_KEY_ID=your-access-key-id
VITE_S3_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY=your-secret-access-key

# SendGrid API Key (if using SendGrid instead of SMTP)
VITE_SENDGRID_API_KEY=your-sendgrid-api-key

# Google Analytics
VITE_GA_TRACKING_ID=your-ga-tracking-id


Users include:

Students taking the exam

Teachers creating questions

Moderators reviewing papers

National exam administrators

Invigilators/proctors

Students → only take exams

Teachers → create questions

Admin → schedule exams

4. Security Layer

National exam systems must protect exam content.

Common security methods:

Encryption of exam questions

Secure servers

Browser lockdown software

AI proctoring (webcam monitoring)

Activity tracking

Some systems also use secure exam browsers like Safe Exam Browser.

5. Proctoring and Monitoring System

This monitors students during the exam.

Tools include:

Webcam monitoring

Screen monitoring

AI cheating detection

Human invigilators


1. Super Administrator

The highest level role that manages the entire platform.

Responsibilities

Create and manage institutions or schools

Create other administrators

Control system settings

Manage security policies

Monitor system usage

Manage backups and infrastructure

Only a few trusted people should have this role.

2. Exam Administrator

This role manages exam operations.

Responsibilities

Create exams

Schedule exam dates and times

Assign exams to schools or students

Approve final exam papers

Monitor exams in progress

Release results


3. Subject Examiner / Question Setter

These are teachers or experts who create questions.

Responsibilities

Add questions to the question bank

Tag questions by:

Subject

Topic

Difficulty

Create marking schemes

They cannot publish exams themselves.

4. Moderator / Reviewer

This role ensures quality control.

Responsibilities

Review questions created by examiners

Correct mistakes

Approve or reject questions

Ensure syllabus coverage

Verify marking schemes

5. Invigilator / Proctor

These users monitor the exam session.

Responsibilities

Start and stop exam sessions

Verify student identity

Monitor cheating

Report suspicious behavior

Assist students during exams

Some systems also use AI proctoring tools like ProctorU.

7. Student / Candidate

This is the exam taker.

Permissions

Log in to the exam system

View assigned exams

Take exams

Submit answers

View results (when released)

Students typically access exams through platforms like Moodle or Blackboard Learn.

8. Institution / School Admin (Optional but common)

If multiple schools use the system, each school has an admin.

Responsibilities

Register students

Manage teachers

Assign students to exams

View school results

9. Technical Support / IT Admin

Handles technical issues.

Responsibilities

Monitor servers

Fix system errors

Manage database

Handle system updates

Support users during exams

✅ Simple Role Structure

Super Admin
     ↓
Exam Administrator
     ↓
---------------------------------
| Question Setter | Moderator   |
---------------------------------
            ↓
        Exam System
            ↓
---------------------------------
| Invigilator | Marker | Student|
---------------------------------

💡 For a real national exam platform, you usually need 8–10 roles to properly separate responsibilities and prevent exam leaks.